e.g.
    query params are actually
    ?param1=+firstname:mike +lastname:ekoka&param2=+firstname:john +lastname:doe

    after encoding:
    <space char>    => +
    +               => %2B
    :               => %3A

    url encoded should thus give
    
    ?param1=%2Bfirstname%3Amike+%2Blastname%3Aekoka&param2=%2Bfirstname%3Ajohn+%2Blastname%3Adoe


to do this with curl:
    
    curl -G 'http://my.url/some/random/path' \
        --data-urlencode 'param1=+firstname:mike +lastname:ekoka' \
        --data-urlencode 'param2=+firstname:john +lastname:doe'

note: the -G option places the data in the query string. see `curl --manual` for more.
